        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "The documentation and class uses the name \"umask\" for what is not an umask (see umask(2) man page for the definition : \"umask()  sets  the calling process's file mode creation mask (umask) to mask & 0777\"). Rather, the Zend_Cache_Backend_File uses the option \"cache_file_umask\" to chmod  (http:\/\/php.net\/chmod) the file. In effect this is an octal permission definition rather than a umask.\r\n\r\nThis is quite misleading."
        },
